author: Prince Imehiron
title: Iwobi Scores Twice As Arsenal Down Bayern
text:
Headlines / Iwobi Scores Twice As Arsenal Down Bayern Iwobi Scores Twice As Arsenal Down Bayern   
Nigerian youngster, Alex Iwobi, was the hero of the day for the Arsenal U-19 side as his two goals sealed a 2-0 victory against Bayern Munich’s U-19s team in a UEFA Youth League clash at Meadows Park on Tuesday. 
After a goalless first half, Iwobi put his side ahead when he opened scoring in the 73rd minute. Iwobi later made it 2-0 for Arsenal U-19s when he struck again in the 78th minute of the encounter. 
He however went into the referee’s book in the 81st minute after an altercation with Bayern’s Friedl. Iwobi featured for the first team of Arsenal during their tour of Asia. 
He also made his debut for the Super Eagles in their international friendly games against DR Congo and Cameroon in Belgium this month.
